25
00:02:38,569 --> 00:02:43,169
but since this is not going
to be a fast-forward merge,

26
00:02:43,169 --> 00:02:47,759
Git will create an additional
commit, which is a merge commit,

27
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:50,689
because both these
branches have different commits.

28
00:02:52,849 --> 00:03:00,180
Instead, what we can do is we
