30
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:15,639
What rebase means is that we want to
change the base of the feature branch,

31
00:03:15,639 --> 00:03:21,430
because when we created this feature
branch, it was on a different commit.

32
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:25,819
Afterwards, there were more
commits in the main branch,

33
00:03:25,819 --> 00:03:28,280
and we want to incorporate those commits.

34
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:33,159
So with this command,
with git rebase main,

35
00:03:33,159 --> 00:03:39,430
what git will do is that it will
pull the new changes in main and

36
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:44,870
put the changes in the feature
branch on top of the main commits.

37
00:03:47,349 --> 00:03:49,349
So we do git rebase main.

38
00:03:51,069 --> 00:03:54,560
And now you can see we
already have file four.

39
00:03:55,719 --> 00:04:04,080
If we do git log, then we have added,
we have this commit added file four.

40
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:08,319
And one thing you would notice
is that how the history looks.

41
00:04:09,099 --> 00:04:11,520
Because we have a commit from main,

42
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:14,969
and then we have the
commits from this feature branch.

43
00:04:15,710 --> 00:04:21,670
So the commit into this feature branch
was put on top of the commits on main.

44
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:33,689
Now, if we merge, in order to merge, we
want to go back to our master branch,

45
00:04:33,689 --> 00:04:35,649
which is our main branch.

46
00:04:37,050 --> 00:04:42,740
And now if I run git
merge my feature branch.

47
00:04:45,189 --> 00:04:51,120
In this case, it will be a fast
forward merge because now I have

48
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:55,350
incorporated the changes of main
branch into the feature branch.

49
00:04:57,540 --> 00:05:01,879
So you can see Git says it's
a fast forward merge because

50
00:05:01,879 --> 00:05:05,850
main did not hide any more
commits when I was merging.

51
00:05:07,310 --> 00:05:08,420
Let's check the Git log.

52
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:12,600
And now you can see how
clear the history looks.

53
00:05:13,319 --> 00:05:18,040
We have main commit, then we have
both the commits of our feature branch.

54
00:05:19,129 --> 00:05:22,370
There is no additional
merge commit created by Git.

